# Integrated Protein Structural Validation and Representative Model Selection Pipeline

Use `protein_model_validation_selection_pipeline.py` to rank protein models and select representative structures for downstream docking, MD simulation, or manuscript reporting.

## Hydrolase/CEH mode

```bash
python protein_model_validation_selection_pipeline.py \
  --metrics-table CEH_combined_model_selection.csv \
  --engine hydrolase \
  --family "alpha/beta hydrolase" \
  --outdir ceh_representative_selection
```

The hydrolase engine prioritizes pocket RMSD, catalytic-distance preservation, HGG/GESAG motif pLDDT, and strict structural validation.

## General mode

```bash
python protein_model_validation_selection_pipeline.py \
  --metrics-table quality_matrices.xlsx \
  --sheet "Table S6" \
  --engine general \
  --outdir general_model_selection
```

The general engine balances MolProbity, CaBLAM, VoroMQA, Foldseek/TMalign similarity, and confidence metrics.

## Outputs

- `all_models_scored.tsv`
- `representative_models.tsv`
- `structural_validation_selection.xlsx`
- `validation_selection_report.md`
- `plots/top_selection_scores.png`
- hydrolase pocket plot when hydrolase metrics are available

## Optional tools

The pipeline can optionally call MolProbity, CaBLAM, VoroMQA, TMalign, and Foldseek if installed.

```bash
python protein_model_validation_selection_pipeline.py \
  --models-dir models \
  --templates-dir templates \
  --convert-cif \
  --run-external-validation \
  --run-tmalign \
  --outdir validation_with_templates
```
